What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend it. But know that it is work. It seems really easy at first, but Toni is a hard grader and you have to write and direct. BUT it is worth it!
In playwright director lab, you write a 2 page scene each week and are assigned a classmates 2 page scene to direct each week. I would recommend it.

In the spirit of Writing About Oneself or another demanding writing class taught by a shrewd and competent wit, I would recommend you take it credit/d, writers and directors of the world. And I would recommend you take it!

Yes, definitely take this course! It's unlike any other at Yale. The students, as much as the professor, determine the character of the course. If you are at all interested in writing or directing for the stage, this seminar will challenge and delight you.
